# Enhanced Social Reactions: Complete Implementation Blueprint

## Patterns and Conventions Found

**Animation:** `framer-motion` with `AnimatePresence` used throughout. Springs: `{ type: 'spring', damping: 20, stiffness: 400 }` for pickers, `{ damping: 25, stiffness: 200 }` for modals. All animations layered over existing DOM, never blocking interaction.

**Mutations:** `client/src/utils/useMutation.js` — every mutation follows the same pattern: optimistic update in `onMutate`, rollback in `onError`, guarded in-flight deduplication via `Set` + `ref`. The `useReactionMutation` at line 408 is the anchor for Feature 1.

**Comments:** Two-file split — `comments.jsx` (section container + submit logic) and `commentsCards.jsx` (recursive card + reply inline). Self-referential recursion: `CommentsCards` renders `CommentsCards` for replies at line 254. CSS namespace: `.cm-*`.

**Opinions system:** `OpinionsEditor.jsx` uses a plain `<textarea>`. `OpinionsCardRepy.jsx` uses `contentEditable` div. Both share `sidebarOpinions.css`.

**Mention in Lexical:** Full `MentionPlugin.jsx` exists at `client/src/components/HomePage/Editor/nodes/Plugins/MentionPlugin.jsx`. It uses `createPortal` + `window.getSelection()` for caret positioning, `searchFollowingUsers` API, 200ms debounce. Plain textareas have no mention support at all.

**Server-side mention processing:** `extractMentions.js` walks Lexical JSON for `type: 'mention'` nodes. Comments are stored as raw strings — no structured format — so server-side mention extraction from comments requires a regex approach, not Lexical AST walking.

**Search:** `GET /users/search` (public, no auth, ilike on name+username) and `GET /users/following/search` (auth required) both exist. The public one fits comment mentions since commenters may not follow the mentioned user.

**CSS variables used:** `--accent-amber`, `--bg-card`, `--bg-pill`, `--border-card`, `--text-faint`, `--text-heading`, `--font-ui`, `--font-serif`. Glass morphism with `backdrop-filter: blur`.

