**Backend: `server/services/interactService.js` — `addCommentService` (already handles replies via `parentId`)**

No structural changes needed. The improvement is adding @mention detection to replies. Add this after the existing `insertCommentPromise` succeeds (non-fatal, same pattern as journal mentions):

```js
// After successful insert, inside addCommentService:
// Non-fatal: detect @username patterns in comment text and notify
try {
    const MENTION_REGEX = /@([\w-]+)/g;
    const usernames = [];
    let m;
    while ((m = MENTION_REGEX.exec(comments)) !== null) {
        usernames.push(m[1].toLowerCase());
    }
    if (usernames.length > 0) {
        const { data: mentionedUsers } = await supabase
            .from('users')
            .select('id')
            .in('username', usernames.slice(0, 10));
        const filtered = (mentionedUsers || [])
            .map(u => u.id)
            .filter(id => id !== userId && id !== receiverId); // skip author + post owner (already notified)
        if (filtered.length > 0) {
            await supabase.from('notifications').insert(
                filtered.map(rid => ({
                    sender_id: userId,
                    receiver_id: rid,
                    journal_id: postId,
                    type: 'mention',
                    read: false,
                }))
            );
        }
    }
} catch (mentionErr) {
    console.error('[comment mentions]', mentionErr?.message);
}
```

**No database schema changes needed** — the 2-level threading is already fully supported by the `parent_id` column on `comments`. The `reply_count` column on the parent comment row is already maintained.

### Data Flow

```
showReplyInput = true
  → ReplyContextChip appears above textarea (animated height)
  → User types reply text (may include @username)
  → submitReply() called
    → optimistic update (existing)
    → addReply() API → POST /submitReply/:parent_id/:user_id/:post_id/:receiver_id
    → Server: addCommentService() inserts comment + notif to post owner
    → Server: regex scans reply text for @usernames → additional mention notifs
  → invalidateQueries(['getPostReplies', parent_id])
  → showReplyInput = false
  → showReplies = true (auto-expand to show the new reply)
```

