## Feature 3: @mention Autocomplete in Comments and Opinions

### Architecture Decision

**Textarea-based mention detection with a portaled floating dropdown.** The Lexical editor already has `MentionPlugin.jsx` which is excellent for reference — but comments and opinions use plain `<textarea>` and `contentEditable` divs, not Lexical. We cannot reuse MentionPlugin directly (it requires `useLexicalComposerContext`). Instead, we build a standalone hook + component pair that works with any text input.

**The autocomplete uses `GET /users/search` (public, no auth) not `searchFollowingUsers`** — because commenters should be able to mention anyone, not just people they follow. The existing `searchUsers` function in `Api.js` (line 81) is a perfect match.

**Debounce: 300ms** (slightly more generous than the Lexical plugin's 200ms to reduce API calls since comment mentions are less latency-critical).

**Insertion:** For `<textarea>`, we manipulate `selectionStart`/`selectionEnd` to replace the `@query` with `@username `. For the `contentEditable` opinion input in `OpinionsCardRepy.jsx`, we use `document.execCommand('insertText')` (cross-browser compatible with existing React Native-like contentEditable pattern) or the Selection API.

### New Files

**`client/src/components/mentions/useMentionAutocomplete.js`**

This is the core hook. It takes a `value` string and `cursorPosition` (from `selectionStart`) and returns `{ query, results, isOpen, selectedIndex, selectMention, closeMenu, setSelectedIndex }`.

```js
// client/src/components/mentions/useMentionAutocomplete.js
import { useState, useEffect, useRef, useCallback } from 'react';
import { searchUsers } from '../../../API/Api';

const MENTION_TRIGGER_REGEX = /@([\w-]*)$/;
const DEBOUNCE_MS = 300;

export function useMentionAutocomplete(value, cursorPosition) {
    const [query, setQuery] = useState(null);       // null = menu closed
    const [results, setResults] = useState([]);
    const [selectedIndex, setSelectedIndex] = useState(0);
    const [isLoading, setIsLoading] = useState(false);
    const debounceRef = useRef(null);

    // Detect @query from text up to cursor
    useEffect(() => {
        if (typeof cursorPosition !== 'number') {
            setQuery(null);
            return;
        }
        const textUpToCursor = value.substring(0, cursorPosition);
        const match = textUpToCursor.match(MENTION_TRIGGER_REGEX);

        if (!match) {
            setQuery(null);
            setResults([]);
            return;
        }

        setQuery(match[1]); // empty string is valid (just "@")
    }, [value, cursorPosition]);

    // Fetch results with debounce
    useEffect(() => {
        if (query === null) {
            setResults([]);
            return;
        }

        if (debounceRef.current) clearTimeout(debounceRef.current);

        if (query.length === 0) {
            // "@" typed with no query yet — don't fetch, show empty
            setResults([]);
            return;
        }

        debounceRef.current = setTimeout(async () => {
            setIsLoading(true);
            try {
                const res = await searchUsers(query, 6);
                setResults(res?.data || []);
                setSelectedIndex(0);
            } catch {
                setResults([]);
            } finally {
                setIsLoading(false);
            }
        }, DEBOUNCE_MS);

        return () => clearTimeout(debounceRef.current);
    }, [query]);

    const closeMenu = useCallback(() => {
        setQuery(null);
        setResults([]);
        setSelectedIndex(0);
    }, []);

    const isOpen = query !== null && (results.length > 0 || (query.length > 0 && isLoading));

    return {
        query,
        results,
        isOpen,
        isLoading,
        selectedIndex,
        setSelectedIndex,
        closeMenu,
    };
}
```

**`client/src/components/mentions/MentionDropdown.jsx`**

Portaled dropdown, identical visual style to the existing Lexical `mention-dropdown` in `MentionPlugin.jsx`. Accepts `{ isOpen, results, selectedIndex, onSelect, onHover, position }`.

```jsx
// client/src/components/mentions/MentionDropdown.jsx
import React from 'react';
import { AnimatePresence, motion } from 'framer-motion';
import { createPortal } from 'react-dom';
import { handleImageFallback } from '../../utils/handleImageFallback';
import './mentionDropdown.css';

const MentionDropdown = ({ isOpen, results, selectedIndex, onSelect, onHover, position }) => {
    if (!isOpen || !position) return null;

    return createPortal(
        <AnimatePresence>
            {isOpen && (
                <motion.div
                    className="mention-dropdown"
                    style={{ top: position.top, left: position.left }}
                    initial={{ opacity: 0, y: -4, scale: 0.97 }}
                    animate={{ opacity: 1, y: 0, scale: 1 }}
                    exit={{ opacity: 0, y: -4, scale: 0.97 }}
                    transition={{ duration: 0.12, ease: 'easeOut' }}
                >
                    {results.map((user, index) => (
                        <div
                            key={user.id}
                            className={`mention-dropdown-item${index === selectedIndex ? ' mention-dropdown-item--selected' : ''}`}
                            onMouseDown={(e) => {
                                e.preventDefault();
                                onSelect(user);
                            }}
                            onMouseEnter={() => onHover(index)}
                        >
                            <img
                                className="mention-dropdown-avatar"
                                src={user.image_url || '/assets/profile.jpg'}
                                alt=""
                                onError={handleImageFallback}
                            />
                            <div className="mention-dropdown-info">
                                <span className="mention-dropdown-name">{user.name}</span>
                                {user.username && (
                                    <span className="mention-dropdown-username">@{user.username}</span>
                                )}
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    ))}
                </motion.div>
            )}
        </AnimatePresence>,
        document.body
    );
};

export default MentionDropdown;
```

